ntreux, Switzerland

January 31, 1973

Dear Mr. Lacy,

I thank you for your letter from The Caravanserai, of January 20. I hope you and Mrs. Lacy have thoroughly enjoyed your holiday.

To-day I can only try to answer the second part of your letter, pertaining to my literary plans.

The only two kinds of "butterfly books" that I could contemplate writing are: i. a learned work with a minimum of text and a maximum of colored photographs on the 400 species (and about 1500 subspecies) of European bu